target.body:
Fixes #65868.

## Summary
- replaces terse QQBot missing-credential errors with setup guidance and docs/credential links
- qualifies named-account missing-credential guidance so operators use `channels.qqbot.accounts.<id>.*` instead of default-only `QQBOT_*` env vars
- preserves raw QQ Open Platform token response details while adding account-neutral guidance for invalid credentials

## Test plan
- `git diff --check`
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-messaging.config.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/gateway.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/messaging/outbound.test.ts` (3 files, 10 tests)
- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/qqbot/src/engine/errors.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/gateway.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/gateway.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/messaging/outbound.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/messaging/outbound.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.test.ts`
- `pnpm exec oxlint extensions/qqbot/src/engine/errors.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/gateway.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/gateway.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/messaging/outbound.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/messaging/outbound.test.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.test.ts`

## Real behavior proof
- Behavior or issue addressed: QQBot setup/auth failures previously surfaced terse messages such as missing credentials or raw token JSON without telling operators where to configure credentials or what QQ Open Platform condition to check. Named accounts also need account-scoped credential paths instead of default-only `QQBOT_*` guidance, and token auth errors need guidance that applies to both default and named accounts.
- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on Linux at current head `ef10dadc036133ce47dbd2e5f2337fa2245e0a0d`.
- Exact steps or command run after this patch:
```bash
node --import tsx --input-type=module <<'EOF'
import { startGateway } from './extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/gateway.ts';
import { sendText } from './extensions/qqbot/src/engine/messaging/outbound.ts';
import { TokenManager } from './extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/token.ts';

const runtime = {
  channel: {
    activity: { record() {} },
    routing: { resolveAgentRoute() {} },
    reply: {
      dispatchReplyWithBufferedBlockDispatcher() {},
      resolveEffectiveMessagesConfig() { return {}; },
      finalizeInboundContext() {},
      formatInboundEnvelope() {},
      resolveEnvelopeFormatOptions() {},
    },
    session: {
      resolveStorePath() { return '/tmp/qqbot-proof-session.jsonl'; },
      recordInboundSession() {},
    },
    inbound: { run() {} },
    text: { chunkMarkdownText(text) { return [text]; } },
  },
  tts: { async textToSpeech() { return { success: false }; } },
};
const adapters = {
  history: {},
  mentionGate: {},
  access: {},
  audioConvert: {},
  outboundAudio: {},
  commands: { resolveVersion: () => 'proof', pluginVersion: 'proof' },
};
const log = { info() {}, error() {}, debug() {} };

async function show(label, fn) {
  try {
    const result = await fn();
    console.log(`--- ${label} ---`);
    console.log(typeof result === 'string' ? result : JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));
  } catch (err) {
    console.log(`--- ${label} ---`);
    console.log(err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err));
  }
}

await show('gateway default missing credentials', () =>
  startGateway({
    account: { accountId: 'default', appId: '', clientSecret: '', markdownSupport: false, config: {} },
    cfg: {},
    runtime,
    adapters,
    abortSignal: new AbortController().signal,
    log,
  }),
);

await show('gateway named account missing clientSecret', () =>
  startGateway({
    account: { accountId: 'ops', appId: 'app-id', clientSecret: '', markdownSupport: false, config: {} },
    cfg: {},
    runtime,
    adapters,
    abortSignal: new AbortController().signal,
    log,
  }),
);

await show('outbound named account missing clientSecret', () =>
  sendText({
    to: 'c2c:user-openid',
    text: 'hello',
    account: { accountId: 'ops', appId: 'app-id', clientSecret: '', markdownSupport: false, config: {} },
  }),
);

await show('token invalid credential response', () =>
  new TokenManager().getAccessToken('00000000000000000000', 'invalid-client-secret'),
);
EOF
```
- Evidence after fix:
```text
Terminal transcript from the real OpenClaw QQBot gateway, outbound, and token paths:
--- gateway default missing credentials ---
QQBot not configured. Set QQBOT_APP_ID and QQBOT_CLIENT_SECRET, or run `openclaw configure`. Get credentials at: https://q.qq.com/ Docs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/channels/qqbot
--- gateway named account missing clientSecret ---
QQBot account "ops" is not configured. Set channels.qqbot.accounts.ops.appId and channels.qqbot.accounts.ops.clientSecret (or clientSecretFile), or run `openclaw configure` for that account. QQBOT_APP_ID and QQBOT_CLIENT_SECRET only configure the default QQBot account. Get credentials at: https://q.qq.com/ Docs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/channels/qqbot
--- outbound named account missing clientSecret ---
{
  "channel": "qqbot",
  "error": "QQBot account \"ops\" is not configured. Set channels.qqbot.accounts.ops.appId and channels.qqbot.accounts.ops.clientSecret (or clientSecretFile), or run `openclaw configure` for that account. QQBOT_APP_ID and QQBOT_CLIENT_SECRET only configure the default QQBot account. Get credentials at: https://q.qq.com/ Docs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/channels/qqbot"
}
--- token invalid credential response ---
Failed to get QQBot access token. Check the QQBot app ID and client secret configured for this account. Get credentials at: https://q.qq.com/ Docs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/channels/qqbot Response: {"code":100007,"message":"appid invalid"}
```
- Observed result after fix: The real QQBot gateway startup path and outbound send path now return actionable setup guidance. Named accounts point at account-scoped config fields, while default-account guidance still names `QQBOT_APP_ID` and `QQBOT_CLIENT_SECRET`. The token path made a live QQ Open Platform request with intentionally invalid credentials and preserved the platform response while using account-neutral app ID/client secret guidance that applies to default and named accounts.
- What was not tested: A successful live QQBot credential exchange was not run because valid QQBot credentials are not available in this environment.
- Proof limitations or environment constraints: The token proof intentionally uses invalid credentials, so the expected live QQ Open Platform response is an authentication error rather than a successful token.
